==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flyswatter
<hw>fly"swat*ter</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>An implement with a flat part (a mesh of metal or plastic) and a
long handle, used to kill insects by striking them. The handle is
typically about one foot long and the flat mesh at the end (usually of
plastic) is about 5 inces square.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> swatter.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flytrap</ent>⟦br⟧
